<h1 class="h1Proj">About Project</h1>
<p>

</p>
<br>
<p>
    My father came to me with an idea on how to improve the inspections for pipelines. The project is to build and program a device that can
    measure the distance of a pipe, while using a lidar and accelerometer to map out the pipelines. The reason why the lidar is needed is to potentially find
    any large cracks or damage within the pipe.<br>
    The device will need to be attached to the back of a crawler that will move down the pipe. A crawler is currently used to inspect pipelines, but it only
    has a low qaulity camera and light attched to it. It is very hard and time consuming to spot damage in the pipe, because the footage from the camera
    needs to be manually viewed by the worker on-site.<br>
    The goal is to make a device that can make it easier and more productive  to inspect pipelines.
</p>

